com.ibm.team.repository.common

Class ConfigurationDataFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.team.repository.common.ConfigurationDataFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConfigurationDataFactory

    public class ConfigurationDataFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements IConfigurationDataFactory
    A utility class providing an implementation of the non-model object 'IConfigurationData' Configuration Aware Data through provided static methods. The primary use of this utility class is for usage with ConfigurationAwareAuditable and ConfigurationAwareSimpleItem working copies, and transport for Configuration Management of Item-specific data in a configuration context: specifically the changeSet usage of an item state within a configuration.

    The following readable features are implemented in the returned IConfigurationData:

    • Internal
    • Ignored
    • Change Set Id

      • make

        public IConfigurationData make(UUID changeSetId,
                               boolean isSetIgnored,
                               boolean ignored,
                               boolean isSetInternal,
                               boolean internal,
                               UUID configId)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. Because this may be used to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are provided. A UUID changeSetId and UUID configId are required, even if matching IConfigurationData the UUID NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT, and so does not have an isSet option. The configId value is just for read-only. This value never saves in the database. TeamServiceContext always takes the precedence and only TeamServiceContext configid value saves in the database while saving the item.
